### Iteration 2 (2026-06-23 second sweep)

- [ ] [feature] Panel layout persistence ŌĆö remember the last-active sub-view (`terminals` / `explore` / `mdns` / `topology` / `todo`) per window and restore on next `activate`. Stored alongside the audit log, but keyed off `workbench.view.extension.superset`. Avoids clashing with VSCode's own `workbench.panel.defaultLocation`. See scan note 2026-06-23#2D.
- [x] [feature] Terminal jump-to via `Superset: Go to Terminal` quick-pick ŌĆö fuzzy pick of all open terminals, used as a `Ctrl+Shift+P` target. Composes with [terminal fuzzy search](plans/2026-06-23-feature-terminal-fuzzy-search.md): the pick reuses the same `matchesTerminal` helper. See scan note 2026-06-23#2E.

### Iteration 3 (2026-06-23 third sweep)

- [x] [feature] mDNS detail-view query cache ŌĆö `MdnsShowDetail` currently re-resolves on every invocation. Cache `buildMdnsDetailFields` output for 60s keyed by `${name}|${type}|${host}|${port}` to avoid spamming mDNS for already-seen services. Pairs with service expiration. See scan note 2026-06-23#3I.
- [ ] [feature] mDNS service dedup by `host|port|type` ŌĆö multi-NIC / IPv4+IPv6 currently produce duplicate rows. `MdnsRegistry` upserts by name but not by network identity; add secondary key so the tree shows one canonical row per service. See scan note 2026-06-23#3J.
- [ ] [feature] `Superset: Open Settings` webview ŌĆö consolidate all `superset.*` settings (audit level, topology scan interval, future group-meta toggle) into one panel, plus a status badge for each panel's source-of-truth (registry / mDNS / topology / todo). See scan note 2026-06-23#3P.

### Iteration 4 (2026-06-23 fourth sweep ŌĆö compatibility baseline)

- [ ] [chore] VSCode baseline alignment ŌĆö bump `engines.vscode` to `^1.90.0` (code already assumes 1.90+ behaviors: `TabInputTerminal`, `Terminal.name` getter-only), pin `@types/vscode` to `~1.90.0`, add `engines.node >=20.0.0`, remove dead `nameWriteSupported` runtime probe in `highlightPresenter.ts`, update docs. See [plans/2026-06-23-chore-vscode-baseline-alignment.md](plans/2026-06-23-chore-vscode-baseline-alignment.md). See scan note 2026-06-23#4A.

### Iteration 4 (2026-06-23 fourth sweep ŌĆö UX self-service)

- [ ] [feature] `Superset: Reveal in Tree` command ŌĆö given a `TerminalHandle`, focus the `superset.terminals` TreeView and select the matching row. Wires `vscode.commands.executeCommand("treeView.reveal", item)` (stable since 1.47). Composes with every panel by reusing the same `(viewId, predicate)` helper. See scan note 2026-06-23#4Q.
- [ ] [feature] `Superset: Reset All Caches` command ŌĆö one-button wipe of `context.workspaceState` keys, mDNS in-memory cache, and `TopologyStore` state. Backs the "something's stale, start over" workflow; cheap (~30 LOC) and unblocks debugging. See scan note 2026-06-23#4U.

### Iteration 5 (2026-06-23 fifth sweep ŌĆö release hygiene)

- [ ] [chore] VSIX cross-platform packaging sanity ŌĆö `.vscodeignore` exclude dev artifacts (test/, src/, scripts/, **/**tests**/**) while intentionally keeping `@homebridge/node-pty-prebuilt-multiarch/prebuilds/` for all target platforms; add `scripts/verify-vsix.sh` that post-checks the .vsix; wire into `npm run build`. See [plans/2026-06-23-chore-vsix-cross-platform-sanity.md](plans/2026-06-23-chore-vsix-cross-platform-sanity.md). See scan note 2026-06-23#5A.

### Iteration 6 (2026-06-24 sixth sweep ŌĆö debugging experience)

- [ ] [chore] `Superset: Show Diagnostics` webview ŌĆö one-click snapshot of every subsystem (terminals / mDNS / topology / todo / engines / activation session), with Copy-to-clipboard and Save-to-file buttons. Complements the existing `superset.showLogs` (time-series log) with a structured "now" view, unblocks GitHub-issue triage. See [plans/2026-06-24-chore-show-diagnostics-webview.md](plans/2026-06-24-chore-show-diagnostics-webview.md). See scan note 2026-06-24#6A.

### Iteration 7 (2026-06-24 seventh sweep ŌĆö continuous integration)

- [ ] [chore] GitHub Actions CI + issue / PR templates ŌĆö add `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (3-OS matrix: macos / ubuntu / windows, runs `npm test` + `tsc --noEmit`), `.github/workflows/coverage.yml` (vitest --coverage to PR artifact), `.github/workflows/release.yml` (tag-triggered `vsce package` for [#5A VSIX sanity](plans/2026-06-23-chore-vsix-cross-platform-sanity.md)); add `ISSUE_TEMPLATE/{bug_report,feature_request}.md`, `PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, README CI badge. See [plans/2026-06-24-chore-github-actions-ci.md](plans/2026-06-24-chore-github-actions-ci.md). See scan note 2026-06-24#7A.

